theorem interior_closure_inter_subset_interiors
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X)) ⊆
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) ∩ interior (closure (B : Set X)) := by
  -- Step 1: `closure (A ∩ B)` is contained in `closure A ∩ closure B`.
  have h₁ :
      closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X) ⊆
        closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    have hxA : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) :=
      (closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
    have hxB : x ∈ closure (B : Set X) :=
      (closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hx
    exact And.intro hxA hxB
  -- Step 2: Apply monotonicity of `interior`.
  have h₂ :
      interior (closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X)) ⊆
        interior (closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X)) :=
    interior_mono h₁
  -- Step 3: Show `interior (S ∩ T)` is contained in `interior S ∩ interior T`.
  have h₃ :
      interior (closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X)) ⊆
        interior (closure (A : Set X)) ∩ interior (closure (B : Set X)) := by
    intro x hx
    rcases mem_interior.1 hx with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsub⟩
    have hU_A : U ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := fun y hy => (hUsub hy).1
    have hU_B : U ⊆ closure (B : Set X) := fun y hy => (hUsub hy).2
    have hxA : x ∈ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
      mem_interior.2 ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hU_A⟩
    have hxB : x ∈ interior (closure (B : Set X)) :=
      mem_interior.2 ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hU_B⟩
    exact And.intro hxA hxB
  exact h₂.trans h₃

theorem clopen_has_all_Ps {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X)) (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 A ∧ Topology.P2 A ∧ Topology.P3 A := by
  -- We can obtain all three properties directly from the fact that `A` is open.
  exact Topology.isOpen_has_all_Ps (X := X) (A := A) hOpen
